# Float Interactive Help Messages
#
# Messages used by Float when generating help texts for its own windows.

Help.IconBar:\TFloating Help application.|MMove the pointer to receive help from other applications.|M\Stoggle help panes on and off.|M\Achange the options.
Help.Info:This \w displays information about Float.
Help.Info.Web:\Sopen the Float home page in your web browser, if one has been seen.

Help.Colours:\Tcolour selection \w.|M\Schoose a colour.

Help.Choices:\TChoices \w for Floating Help.|MYou can use it to change the way Floating Help operates.
Help.Choices.Cancel:\Sclose the choices \w and forget any changes made.|M\Areset any changes made so far and start again.
Help.Choices.Save:\Sclose the choices \w, using the changes and saving them to disc.|M\Ause the changes and save them.
Help.Choices.Apply:\Sclose the choices \w and use the changes|M\Ause the changes.
Help.Choices.Display:\Sset options concerning the display of help panes and the types of messages shown.
Help.Choices.Appearance:\Sset options concerning the font and colours used in the help panes.
Help.Choices.Ignore:\Sset a list of tasks for which Floating Help will ignore all interactive help.

Help.Choices0.Open:\Stoggle the display of help panes: this sets the default state for the iconbar icon.|MThe delay before panes open can be set on the right.
Help.Choices0.AutoClose:\Stoggle the automatic closing of help panes after a given time has elapsed.|MThe delay can be set on the right.
Help.Choices0.ActionClose:\Stoggle the closing of help panes when a key is pressed or a mouse button is clicked.
Help.Choices0.DragClose:\Stoggle whether panes are re-opened when a drag is completed.
Help.Choices0.OpenTime:\Ttime in seconds that the mouse must be still for before a help pane is opened.|M\Senter a new time.
Help.Choices0.CloseTime:\Ttime in seconds that a help pane will stay open if the mouse is not moved and Auto close panes is ticked.|M\Sto enter a new time.
Help.Choices0.Furniture:\Stoggle help for \w furniture on and off.|MThis can be overridden with 'Show all' in the icon-bar menu.
Help.Choices0.IBar:\Stoggle help for icons on the icon bar on and off.|MThis can be overridden with 'Show all' in the icon-bar menu.
Help.Choices0.Default:\Stoggle whether or not basic help is shown for tasks that do not respond to the help request.|MThis can be overridden with 'Show all' in the icon-bar menu.
Help.Choices1.FontM:\Schose a font to display the help text.
Help.Choices1.Font:\Tfont used to display the help text.|MClick \s on the right to choose another font.
Help.Choices1.FontSize:\Tsize of the display font, in points.|M\Senter a new size.
Help.Choices1.FontAspect:\Taspect ratio of the display font (width to height).|M\Senter a new ratio.
Help.Choices1.DeskFont:\Stoggle whether or not the standard desktop font is used to display help text, instead of the outline font shown above.
Help.Choices1.ColText:\Tcolour that the text is printed in help panes.|MClick \s on the right to change the colour.
Help.Choices1.ColTextM/Help.Choices1.ColBackM/Help.Choices1.ColShadowM:\Schange the colour of the option on the left.
Help.Choices1.ColBack:\Tcolour of the help pane backgrounds.|MClick \s on the right to change the colour.
Help.Choices1.ColShadow:\Tcolour of the shadows under the help panes, if seleted for display.|MClick \s on the right to change the colour.
Help.Choices1.Shadows:\Stoggle the shadows under the help panes on and off.
Help.Choices2.Name:Enter the name of an application whose help texts are to be ignored by Float, and click \s on Add to add it to the list above.|MClick \s on the pop-up menu button to the right to get a list of name of currently-running applications.
Help.Choices2.Menu:\Sget a list of the names of all the currently-running applications.
Help.Choices2.Add:\Sadd the application name from the field on the left to the list of ignored applications.
Help.Choices2.Remove:\Sremove the highlighted entries from the list of ignored applications.
Help.Ignore:\Tlist of applications whose help texts will be ignored by Float.|M\Shighlight the entry under the mouse. \Aalter an entry's highlight.|MHighlighted entries can be removed from the list by clicking \s on Remove to the right.

Help.IconBarMenu.00:\Rsee information about Float and visit its website for updates.
Help.IconBarMenu.01:\Sread the online documentation for Float.
Help.IconBarMenu.02:\Schange the Floating Help options.
Help.IconBarMenu.03:\Stoggle whether help is shown for all parts of the Desktop, regardless of the settings applied in Choices.
Help.IconBarMenu.04:\Squit Float.

Help.FontMenu.??:\Schoose this font to display the help text.

Help.TaskMenu.??:\Senter this task's name into the new task name field.

# Help Messages For General Use
#
# Messages used by Float when generating default help texts for other tasks.

Default.IconBar:\T%0 icon.
Default.Window:This is a %0 \w.

# Window Furniture Help
#
# Messages used by Float when generating help texts for window furniture.

Furniture.I2:\TBACK icon.|M\Smove the \w to the bottom of the pile of \ws.
Furniture.I3:\TCLOSE icon.|M\Sclose the \w.
Furniture.I4:\TTitle bar.|M\Sbring the \w to the top.|M\Dmove the \w around the desktop.|M\dmove the \w without affecting the order of \ws.
Furniture.I5:\TTOGGLE SIZE icon.|M\Stoggle the \w size between full size and the last size displayed.
Furniture.I6:\Sscroll the \w up.
Furniture.I7:\Tvertical scroll bar.
Furniture.I8:\Sscroll the \w down.
Furniture.I9:\T\a SIZE icon.|M\Dalter the size and shape of the \w.
Furniture.I10:\Sscroll the \w left.
Furniture.I11:\Thorizontal scroll bar.
Furniture.I12:\Sscroll the \w right.
Furniture.I13:\Tedge of the \w.
Furniture.I14:\TICONISE icon.|M\Siconise the \w.

